+## Page Objects Needed
+
+### New PO Methods on `ChatPo` (`cypress/e2e/po/chat.po.ts`)
+
+```typescript
+openViaKeyboard() {
+  const isMac = Cypress.platform === 'darwin';
+  // Use cy.trigger on body so the event bubbles through the DOM to document-level listeners.
+  // win.dispatchEvent fires at window level and does NOT propagate to document-level handlers
+  // (where Rancher Shell's addAction shortcut handler is registered).
+  if (isMac) {
+    cy.get('body').trigger('keydown', { metaKey: true, shiftKey: true, key: 'k', keyCode: 75, bubbles: true, cancelable: true });
+  } else {
+    cy.get('body').trigger('keydown', { altKey: true, key: 'k', keyCode: 75, bubbles: true, cancelable: true });
+  }
+  this.isOpen();
+}
+
+closeViaKeyboard() {
+  const isMac = Cypress.platform === 'darwin';
+  if (isMac) {
+    cy.get('body').trigger('keydown', { metaKey: true, shiftKey: true, key: 'k', keyCode: 75, bubbles: true, cancelable: true });
+  } else {
+    cy.get('body').trigger('keydown', { altKey: true, key: 'k', keyCode: 75, bubbles: true, cancelable: true });
+  }
+  this.isClosed();
+}
+```
+
+These methods encapsulate the platform-aware shortcut. Specs should call `chat.openViaKeyboard()` and `chat.closeViaKeyboard()` rather than inlining keyboard dispatch directly.
+
+**Important**: Use `cy.get('body').trigger('keydown', {...})` — NOT `cy.get('body').type('{alt}k')` (modifier keys unreliable) and NOT `win.dispatchEvent(...)` (doesn't reach document-level listeners). Evidence: Test 5 uses `.trigger('keydown', { altKey: true, key: 'k', keyCode: 75 })` on the textarea and passes consistently.
+
